* text=auto
.vsconfig text eol=lf
*.meta text eol=lf
*.asset text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.txt text eol=lf
*.inputactions text eol=lf
# this line is specifically to deal with auto-generated unity scripts
# unity generates them with LF line endings and opening them with VS likes to convert them to CRLF
# this prevents that.
# all other .cs scripts can stay CRLF since visual studio by defaults uses that.
*Actions.cs text eol=lf 